        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-02-11 01:26:29.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-02-11 04:01:13.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-1013 obdclass: lu_object_find miss to unlink object from LRU",
        "message": "LU-1013 obdclass: lu_object_find miss to unlink object from LRU\n\nThere is race condition between lu_object_find and lu_object_put.\nFor the case of two threads trying to find some object with the\nsame FID concurrently, and the object is not allocated in memory\nyet, if the first thread adds the object into LRU list before the\nsecond thread re-searching object hash table for inserting the\nnew object created by itself, then the second thread will find\nthe object created by the first thread. Under such case, the\nsecond thread should unlink the object from LRU.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <yong.fan@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Iadec96c27d5285f8b859b0060a6f611e87585789\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
